{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492552","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492552"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:35:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:35:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1096"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1096"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.17,0.02,0.7,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1096"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115639"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1096"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1096"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97642"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"21"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"665"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"2589"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8462"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8468"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40320"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49125"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115639"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 74-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with acute onset of chest pain. On examination, his blood pressure is 167/95 mmHg and heart rate 110/mn. The heart sounds are normal and his chest is clear. The ECG shows sinus tachycardia with non-specific ST changes. A CT with contrast is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Coarctation of the aorta","Thoracic aortic aneurysm","Truncus arteriosus","Aortic dissection","Aortitis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has an \u003Cstrong\u003Eaortic dissection\u003C/strong\u003E that originates in the aortic arch. The scans show a type B dissection beginning just beyond the left subclavian artery (see figure below). The true lumen in the abdomen is collapsed but supplies all renal and mesenteric vessels. The dissection extends into the iliac arteries bilaterally, with the right supplied by the false lumen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoarctation of the aorta\u003C/strong\u003E is a congenital narrowing of the aorta, typically diagnosed in paediatric patients. This patient is 74 years old, and although the aorta is narrowed, this is secondary to the expanding false lumen of the dissection, not a congenital defect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThoracic aortic aneurysm \u003C/strong\u003Eis typically asymptomatic and chronic and found incidentally. This diagnosis does not fit with the CT finding of a double-lumen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETruncus arteriosus \u003C/strong\u003Eis a congenital heart defect in which the vessel fails to divide into the aorta and the pulmonary trunk. There is no evidence on CT scan and this a paediatric pathology which does not affect this age group.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAortitis \u003C/strong\u003Emay put a patient at risk of aortic dissection, however there is no evidence of aortitis on this CT scan and is not the most likely diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Suspect aortic dissection in patients with chest pain radiating to the back and hypertension"],"references":["Gaillard F, Worsley C, Rasuli B, et al. Aortic dissection. Reference article, Radiopaedia.org https://doi.org/10.53347/rID-918"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97642"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1096"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19575"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"22136"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19575","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19575"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/817a5a35-b8e3-48b8-99d4-fcd4670c97b9.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/817a5a35-b8e3-48b8-99d4-fcd4670c97b9.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":295,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"22136","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/22136"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ooA6xiGfbbztlQAlSj9bg4wZ2Vv7Sa.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ooA6xiGfbbztlQAlSj9bg4wZ2Vv7Sa.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":295,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97642","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97642"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-24T18:20:39+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-24T18:21:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1096"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115639"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemC